from Titration import SpecData
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

d1 = SpecData('20191122_ArachadonicaAcid_BM3WT_Titration.csv')
d2 = SpecData('20191122_ArachadonicaAcid_BM3WT_Titration_2.csv')
d3 = SpecData('20191122_ArachadonicaAcid_BM3WT_Titration_3.csv')
d4 = SpecData('20191122_ArachadonicaAcid_BM3WT_Titration_4.csv')
d5 = SpecData('20191122_ArachadonicaAcid_BM3WT_Titration_5.csv')

metrics = {}
for j,i in enumerate((d1, d2, d3, d4, d5), 1):
    i.plot_traces(i.data)
    i.plot_traces(i.Diff)
    i.PlotMichaelesMenten()
    km, vmax, loss = i.FitMichaelisMenten()
    temp = {'Km':km.item(), 'Vmax':vmax.item(), 'Loss':loss.item()}
    metrics[j] = temp

def PercentHighSpin(traces):
    return ((103.3 *traces.loc[:,391]) - (42.8 * traces.loc[:,417]))/\
    (traces.loc[:,391]*(103.3-54.5) - traces.loc[:,417]*(42.8-92.4))

import torch 
import torch.nn as nn
from tqdm import tqdm
from torch.utils.data import Dataset, DataLoader
from tqdm import tqdm

from sklearn.preprocessing import MinMaxScaler, StandardScaler, Normalizer, RobustScaler
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.preprocessing import PolynomialFeatures
from sklearn.metrics import r2_score

x = Triton_metrics[['Protein Conc', 'Protein Vol','Time','Triton']].values
#y = (plate_metrics[['Km']]-10.22).abs().values 
y = Triton_metrics[['Noise']]

STD_scaler = StandardScaler()
MM_scaler = MinMaxScaler()
normalizer = Normalizer()
R_scaler = RobustScaler()

x = MM_scaler.fit_transform(x)
y = MM_scaler.fit_transform(y)

poly = PolynomialFeatures(2,include_bias=False)
x = poly.fit_transform(x)

x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(x, y, test_size=0.3)
x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = torch.tensor(x_train,dtype=torch.float),\
torch.tensor(x_test,dtype=torch.float), \
torch.tensor(y_train,dtype=torch.float), \
torch.tensor(y_test,dtype=torch.float)

class dataset(Dataset):
    def __init__(self, x,y):
        self.x = x
        self.y = y
    def __getitem__(self, index):
        return self.x[index], self.y[index]

    def __len__(self):
        return self.x.shape[0]

train_loader = DataLoader(dataset=dataset(x_train,y_train),
                          batch_size=32,
                          shuffle=True,
                          num_workers=0)

model = nn.Linear(x.shape[1],1)

def r_squared_loss(y,yh):
    residuals = y-yh
    ss_res = (residuals**2).sum()
    ss_tot = ((y-y.mean())**2).sum()
    r_squared = 1 - (ss_res / ss_tot)
    return r_squared
    
loss_fn = nn.MSELoss()
opt = torch.optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=1e-4)

loss_record = []

for epoch in tqdm(range(5000)):
    for i, batch in enumerate(train_loader, 0):
        x_,y_ = batch
        yhat = model.forward(x_)
        loss = loss_fn(y_,yhat)
        loss.backward()
        opt.step()
        opt.zero_grad()

        loss_record.append(loss.item())

yhat = model.forward(x_train)
loss = loss_fn(y_train,yhat)
print(f'Training MSE= {round(loss.item(),4)}')

yhat = model.forward(x_test)
err = loss_fn(y_test,yhat)
print(f'Test MSE = {round(err.item(),4)}')
print(f'Test RMSE = {round(err.sqrt().item(),4)}')

plt.figure(figsize=(5,5))                       
plt.plot(np.array(loss_record),lw=0.5,alpha =0.5)
plt.xlabel('Iteration')
plt.ylabel('Mean Squared Error')
plt.show()

plt.figure(figsize=(4,4))
plt.scatter(yhat.detach(),y_test.detach(),alpha = 1, s =5)
plt.plot([0,1],[0,1])
plt.xlabel('Predicted')
plt.ylabel('Actual')
#plt.xlim((0,1))
#plt.ylim((0,1))
plt.show()

print('Rsq t = ',(r_squared_loss(y_test.detach(),yhat.detach())).item())
print('Rsq = ',r2_score(y_test.detach(),yhat.detach()))
